init_text: Your entire life, you've been told you're deathly allergic to bees. You've always had people protecting you from them, be it your mother or a hired hand. Today, one slips through and lands on your shoulder. You hear a tiny voice say "Your Majesty, what are your orders?"

actions.name: text-insert
actions.text: A ladybug sitting on a nearby flower watches you and thinks to herself, "If I were in his place, I'd run for it."

actions.name: text-insert
actions.text: You ask this very question to the bee.

actions.name: text-insert
actions.text: Since you are a human however, you are probably incapable of handling the pressure.

actions.name: text-insert
actions.text: Though you are still doubtful, you are charmed by the bee's persistence.

actions.name: text-insert
actions.text: You're astonished by the intricacies of bee society.

actions.name: text-insert
actions.text: You spend many hours talking to the bees about their problems and their aspirations.

actions.name: text-insert
actions.text: The bees are overjoyed, and they begin preparations immediately.
